de.boereck.matcher.function.predicate

Interface AdvDoublePredicate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DoublePredicate
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface AdvDoublePredicate
extends DoublePredicate
    This extended DoublePredicate provides more default methods as boolean operators.

    • Method Detail

      • ifThen

        default <O> DoubleFunction<Optional<O>> ifThen(DoubleFunction<O> f)
                                        throws NullPointerException
        Applies this predicate as a precondition for the given function f. The returned function will return an empty optional if this predicate evaluates to false for an input. Otherwise the returned function will return an optional holding the output of the wrapped function f for the given input.
        Exceptions thrown by this predicate or function f will thrown to the user of the returned method. If this predicate returns false then f will not be executed, so no Exception will be thrown from f. If this predicate throws an Exception f will not be called.
        Type Parameters:
        O - Type of output object of the wrapped function.
        Parameters:
        f - wrapped mapping function. It will only be called if the predicate returns true for a given input.
        Returns:
        Function that will either return an empty optional (if this predicate returns false for an input), or an optional holding the output of function f (if this predicate returns true for an input).
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if f is null.

      • ifThenFlat

        default <O> DoubleFunction<Optional<O>> ifThenFlat(DoubleFunction<Optional<O>> f)
                                            throws NullPointerException
        Applies this predicate as a precondition for the given function f. The returned function will return an empty optional if this predicate evaluates to false for an input. Otherwise the returned function will return the optional returned by the wrapped function f for the given input.
        Exceptions thrown by this predicate or function f will thrown to the user of the returned method. If this predicate returns false then f will not be executed, so no Exception will be thrown from f. If this predicate throws an Exception f will not be called.
        Type Parameters:
        O - Type of value held by optional-output of the wrapped function.
        Parameters:
        f - wrapped mapping function. It will only be called if the predicate returns true for a given input.
        Returns:
        Function that will either return an empty optional (if this predicate returns false for an input), or the optional returned by function f (if this predicate returns true for an input).
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if f is null.

      • xor

        default AdvDoublePredicate xor(DoublePredicate that)
                        throws NullPointerException
        Returns a predicate, returning the logical XOR of the outputs of this predicate and predicate that.

        Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either predicate are thrown to the caller of the returned combined predicate. If this predicate throws an Exception that predicate will not be evaluated.

        This is the truth table of the returned predicate:

        Output this Output that Output returned
        Parameters:
        that - other predicate that returns that second argument of the logical XOR operation performed by the returned predicate.
        Returns:
        predicate performing a logical XOR operation with the result of this predicate and that predicate.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if that is null.

      • xnor

        default AdvDoublePredicate xnor(DoublePredicate that)
                         throws NullPointerException
        Returns a predicate that provides the logical equality (XNOR) of this predicate and that predicate. This means the returned predicate will return true if the output of this predicate and predicate that provide the same output for the same input object. For all other inputs the returned predicate will return false.

        Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of either predicate are thrown to the caller of the returned combined predicate. If this predicate throws an Exception that predicate will not be evaluated.

        This is the truth table of the returned predicate:

        Output this Output that Output returned
        Parameters:
        that - other predicate that returns that second argument of the logical XNOR operation performed by the returned predicate.
        Returns:
        predicate performing a logical NOR operation with the result of this predicate and that predicate.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if that is null.

      • boxed

        default Predicate<Double> boxed()
        Predicate with the same operation as this working on the boxed data type instead of on the primitive/value types. If the input to the returned predicate is null, the predicate will return false.

        Any exceptions thrown during evaluation of this predicate are thrown to the caller of the returned predicate.

        Returns:
        predicate with the same operation as this, but working on the respective boxed data type.
